Docs.typeparam: The type of element stored in the set.
Docs.summary:
Represents a set of elements that can only be modified by creating a new instance of the set.
[!INCLUDE[immutable_nuget_short](~/includes/immutable-nuget-short-md.md)]

remarks.format: ## Remarks Mutations on this set generate new sets. Incremental changes to a set share as much memory as possible with the prior versions of a set, while allowing garbage collection to clean up any unique set data that is no longer being referenced.
